<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 02 at 3:46PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Cold front with showers to move through before 6 PM...
A cold front will continue to push eastward across Hill, Blaine
and Chouteau counties through 6 PM. Expect some rain showers at
lower elevations and a rain or snow shower at higher elevations
through 6 PM.
Rainfall will be light, generally less than 0.05 inches. However,
expect some wind gusts around 35 mph as the front moves through,
along with falling temperatures from the 60s into the 40s.</description>
